This paper is about speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses optimization techniques and uses Monte Carlo sampling, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves statistical modeling and probability theory, which are relevant to the sub-category of statistics (cs.SD). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing performance metrics, which is a topic in systems and control (cs.SY). However, since the focus of the paper is on speech recognition and NLP, the sub-categories of cs.CL and cs.SD are the most likely.
